description:
In¬† the fall of 2009, Warner Brothers announced that DC Comics become a subsidiary of DC Entertainment, Inc.¬† President of the film subsidiary Warner Premiere, Diane Nelson would not be the President of this newly formed company.
¬†
Former President and Publisher Paul Levitz would move over to the position of Contributing Editor and Overall Consultant, before stepping down as publisher and becoming a writer. deck: Amin provides a wide amplitude of creative services ranging from graphic and web design to comicbook illustration. With a BFA from the School of Visual Arts, NYC and a 2 year hands on apprenticeship under his belt, he has tackled many projects both large and small. With tastes and preferences that are as eclectic as his background, he utilizes this gamut into his artwork as well as in the projects he chooses.
description: In 2011, Amin teamed with fellow artist Gerry Kissell, and the two immediately created the Alan Wake graphic novel for Xbox, and then did the mini series movie tie-in comic for the film Iron Sky, as well as the best selling IDW graphic novel CODE WORD: GERONIMO.
name: Amin Amat
